\section*{Deliverable 5 (v0.1): Local Remainders $\Longrightarrow$ Shell Flux Attempt (Matching $\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{conv}},\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}$ to $\Pi_k$)}

\subsection*{0. Purpose}

This deliverable attempts the \emph{matching step} between the local LEI decomposition (Deliverable~4) and the
frequency-shell flux picture (Deliverable~3). Concretely, we seek to relate the localized remainders


\[
\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{conv}}(x_0,k),\quad \mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}(x_0,k)
\]


to shell fluxes $\Pi_j$ (or weighted sums of $|\Pi_j|$) in a way compatible with dyadic parabolic boxes and the
Carleson endpoint.

The schematic target is:


\[
\boxed{\text{LEI $\Rightarrow$ local dissipation $\le$ cutoff + conv + prs (Deliverable 4)}}\ \Longrightarrow\
\boxed{\text{conv/prs remainders $\lesssim$ shell flux sums}}\ \Longrightarrow\
\boxed{\text{Attempt Lemma 3.3 (local flux $\to$ Carleson)}}.
\]



\subsection*{1. Objects in play (from Deliverables 3 and 4)}

From Deliverable~3 (v0.4):
\begin{itemize}
  \item Shell energy/dissipation/flux:
  

\[
  E_k(t) := \|u_k(t)\|_{L^2_x}^2,\quad
  D_k(t) := \|\nabla u_k(t)\|_{L^2_x}^2,\quad
  \Pi_k(t) := -\langle \Delta_k \mathbb{P}\nabla\cdot(u\otimes u),u_k\rangle.
  \]


  \item Shell balance:
  

\[
  \frac12 \frac{d}{dt}E_k(t) + \nu D_k(t) = \Pi_k(t).
  \]


  \item Dyadic Carleson target:
  

\[
  \|\nabla u\|_{\mathcal{C}_{\mathrm{dyad}}(0,T)}^2
  :=
  \sup_{x_0,k} 2^k \int_0^{\min\{T,2^{-2k}\}}\int_{B(x_0,c2^{-k})} |\nabla u|^2\,dx\,dt.
  \]


\end{itemize}

From Deliverable~4 (v0.1):
\begin{itemize}
  \item Local LEI-based decomposition on a parabolic box centered at $(x_0,k)$:
  

\[
  2^k \int_0^{\tau_k}\!\!\int_{B(x_0,2^{-k})} |\nabla u|^2
  \;\le\;
  C\Big(E_0 + \mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{cut}}(x_0,k) + \mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{conv}}(x_0,k) + \mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}(x_0,k)\Big),
  \]


  with $\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{cut}}$ controlled by $CE_0$ and
  

\[
  \mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{conv}}(x_0,k)
  := 2^k \Big|\int_0^{\tau_k}\!\!\int |u|^2 u\cdot\nabla\phi_{x_0,k}\Big|,
  \quad
  \mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}(x_0,k)
  := 2^k \Big|\int_0^{\tau_k}\!\!\int 2p\,u\cdot\nabla\phi_{x_0,k}\Big|.
  \]


\end{itemize}

\subsection*{2. Attempt: frequency localization of the convective remainder}

We write $u = \sum_j u_j$ with $u_j := \Delta_j u$ and $S_{j-1}u := \sum_{\ell<j} u_\ell$. Using Bony’s
paraproduct decomposition on $u\otimes u$,


\[
u\otimes u = \sum_j \big( S_{j-1}u \otimes u_j + u_j \otimes S_{j-1}u + R_j(u,u)\big),
\]


and the Leray projection $\mathbb{P}$, the shell flux $\Pi_k$ captures the interaction of $u$ with $\Delta_k$ of
$\mathbb{P}\nabla\cdot(u\otimes u)$.

\paragraph{Heuristic matching.}
Formally, one expects that the localized convective term


\[
\int |u|^2 u\cdot\nabla\phi_{x_0,k}
\]


can be expressed (up to commutators and lower-order terms) as a sum over $j\ge k$ of contributions involving
$\Pi_j$ weighted by spatial localization around $x_0$ and time localization on $[0,\tau_k]$.

\paragraph{Attempt Lemma 5.1 (convective remainder $\to$ shell flux sum; heuristic form).}
For each $(x_0,k)$,
\begin{equation}\label{eq:attempt-lemma-5-1}
\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{conv}}(x_0,k)
\;\lesssim\;
2^k \int_0^{\tau_k} \sum_{j\ge k} 2^{-\alpha(j-k)} |\Pi_j(t)|\,dt
\;+\;
\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{comm}}(x_0,k),
\end{equation}
for some $\alpha>0$ (decay in $j-k$) and an error term $\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{comm}}$ built from commutators
between $\Delta_j$, $\mathbb{P}$, and $\phi_{x_0,k}$.

\medskip
\noindent
\emph{Status.} This is an \textbf{attempt} statement: the decay exponent $\alpha$ and the structure of
$\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{comm}}$ are not justified here. The goal is to isolate the exact place where localization and
frequency decomposition interact.

\subsection*{3. Attempt: pressure remainder via Riesz transforms and commutators}

Using $p = \mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j(u_i u_j)$ (Riesz transforms on $\mathbb{T}^3$), we rewrite


\[
\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}(x_0,k)
= 2^k \left|\int_0^{\tau_k}\!\!\int 2\,\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j(u_i u_j)\,u\cdot\nabla\phi_{x_0,k}\right|.
\]



\paragraph{Commutator decomposition.}
Formally,


\[
\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j(u_i u_j)\,u\cdot\nabla\phi
=
\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j\big((u_i u_j) u\cdot\nabla\phi\big)
+
[\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j,\phi](u_i u_j)\,u\cdot\nabla\phi,
\]


where $[\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j,\phi]$ is the commutator. The first term is morally of the same type as the
convective remainder; the second is a genuinely nonlocal localization error.

\paragraph{Attempt Lemma 5.2 (pressure remainder $\to$ shell flux + commutators; heuristic form).}
For each $(x_0,k)$,
\begin{equation}\label{eq:attempt-lemma-5-2}
\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}(x_0,k)
\;\lesssim\;
2^k \int_0^{\tau_k} \sum_{j\ge k} 2^{-\beta(j-k)} |\Pi_j(t)|\,dt
\;+\;
\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{prs-comm}}(x_0,k),
\end{equation}
for some $\beta>0$ and a commutator error $\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{prs-comm}}$ involving
$[\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j,\phi_{x_0,k}]$.

\medskip
\noindent
\emph{Status.} Again, this is an \textbf{attempt} statement: the decay $\beta$ and the precise control of
$\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{prs-comm}}$ are not established.

\subsection*{4. Combined target: local flux $\to$ Carleson (Attempt Lemma 3.3)}

If \eqref{eq:attempt-lemma-5-1} and \eqref{eq:attempt-lemma-5-2} held with:
\begin{itemize}
  \item summable decay in $j-k$ (e.g.\ $\alpha,\beta>0$),
  \item commutator errors $\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{comm}}$, $\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{prs-comm}}$ controlled by $CE_0$ or
  by the same shell-flux sums,
\end{itemize}
then combining Deliverable~4 with these bounds would yield a localized inequality of the form


\[
2^k \int_0^{\tau_k}\!\!\int_{B(x_0,2^{-k})} |\nabla u|^2
\;\lesssim\;
E_0 + \int_0^T \sum_{j\ge k} 2^{j/2} |\Pi_j(t)|\,dt,
\]


which is exactly the structure of Attempt Lemma~3.3 in Deliverable~3.

\subsection*{5. Obstruction (matching step)}

The main obstructions in turning the above heuristic into a theorem are:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Borderline commutators.}
  The operators $\Delta_j$, $\mathbb{P}$, and $\mathcal{R}_i\mathcal{R}_j$ do not commute with multiplication by
  $\phi_{x_0,k}$. The resulting commutators are nonlocal and scale critically with $2^k$.

  \item \textbf{Lack of clean scale separation.}
  The parabolic box $(x_0,k)$ couples spatial scale $2^{-k}$ and time scale $2^{-2k}$, while the shell flux
  $\Pi_j$ is defined globally in space. Localizing $\Pi_j$ to $B(x_0,2^{-k})$ without losing control at critical
  scaling is nontrivial.

  \item \textbf{Intermittency and concentration.}
  Even if one can express $\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{conv}}$ and $\mathcal{R}_{\mathrm{prs}}$ in terms of shell fluxes,
  nothing in the Leray–Hopf or suitable framework prevents concentration of flux in a sparse set of boxes
  $(x_0,k)$, which is exactly what the Carleson endpoint is designed to rule out.
\end{itemize}

